# Tech Context

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Choice | Notes |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Language | TypeScript | All source, mockup, and test files |
| UI Framework | React | BA mockups (`*.tsx` in `ba/req/`) and Dev components (`dev/src/`) |
| Test Automation | Playwright or Cypress | QC automation scripts in `qc/test/` |
| Data Format | JSON | Static mock data in `ba/req/`; test payloads in `qc/test/` |

## Runtime Environments
- **OS**: Windows 10+ (primary dev environment)
- **Node.js**: LTS (required once project dependencies are installed)
- **IDE**: Cursor with Agent mode for spec-driven workflows

## Local Setup
```bash
# Install dependencies (once package.json is added)
npm install

# Run dev server (once configured)
npm run dev

# Run tests (once configured)
npm test
```

## File Conventions
- **BA outputs**: `features/Feature-N/ba/req/` — static mockups, JSON data, BSR markdown
- **Dev outputs**: `features/Feature-N/dev/src/` — production React components, utils, API handlers
- **QC outputs**: `features/Feature-N/qc/test/` — test cases, test data, automation scripts

## Constraints
- BA mock data must never connect to live APIs or database clients
- Dev code must ground against `ba/req/FeatureNBSR.md`, mockups, and mock data before implementation
- QC tests must read both `ba/` requirements and `dev/` source code
